            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am disappointed with my experience at Shalom Hills International School. The school management has been ineffective in addressing several issues, including the partial staff and the lack of focus on sports. The quality of teaching is average at best, with most of the teachers struggling with English. The classrooms are in bad condition and the school buses are often broken. The school seems to lack excellence in any particular area, with facilities and resources falling short of expectations. It's concerning to see some teachers raise their hands at students, which is not an acceptable way to discipline children. The vice-principal is also known to be rude and unapproachable. Lastly, students are burdened with too much homework and the workload is not balanced with other activities. I hope the school can address these issues and improve its standards. Also no ac is working and condition of class is not good its very dirty and not well maintained.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
